The paper discusses dialogue systems that use knowledge bases, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) communities, suggesting cs.CL and cs.AI as likely categories. The paper also proposes a method for continuous learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (ML) and reinforcement learning (RL), making cs.LG a likely category. The paper also deals with knowledge representation and inference, which are topics in information retrieval (IR) and databases (DB), making cs.IR and cs.DB likely categories as well.
